  "body": "<!--\r\nNeed help?\r\nRefer to our contributing guidelines for additional information about making a good issue:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/.github/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\nAfter starting optimism node in docker-comppose, gas-oracle exited almost immediately\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. git clone https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism.git -b develop\r\n2. cd optimism/ops\r\n3. docker-compose -f docker-compose-nobuild.yml up -t 600 -d (or docker-compose -f docker-compose.yml up -d --build --force-recreate - it does not matter)\r\n4. docker ps -a\r\n5. docker logs ID_OF_EXITED_GAS_ORACLE\r\n\r\n```\r\nERROR[03-09|10:23:43.193] Unable to connect to layer two           addr=http://127.0.0.1:9545\r\nCRIT [03-09|10:23:43.197] application failed                       message=\"Post \\\"http://127.0.0.1:9545\\\": dial tcp 127.0.0.1:9545: connect: connection refused\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nLooks like Sequencer HTTP Endpoint (GAS_PRICE_ORACLE_LAYER_TWO_HTTP_URL) is not set properly.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\ngas-oracle start successfully\r\n\r\n",
